Pre-Game Insights: Ryan Ayte Nori and Mohamed Amin Amoura are out of the Algeria squad to face Liberia on September 10, 2024 in the AFCON qualifiers.
Others: The two Algerian professional footballers pick-up straight injuries today and the team's medical staff has decided to allow the players to stay and recover without risking their health.
New Injuries: Ryan Ayte Nori and Mohamed Amin Amoura are injured and will return to their respective clubs starting on Saturday.
Team Updates: The rest of the team will continue their preparations at the Sidi Musa National Technical Center before departing for Liberia on Sunday at 14:30.
Player Absences: Ryan Ayte Nori and Mohamed Amin Amoura will not play for Algeria on September 10, 2024.
